# createRoute function 

![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)Copy page

![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)

![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)

<div>

The [createRoute] function implements returns a [[Route]](/router/latest/docs/framework/react/api/router/RouteType) instance. A route instance can then be passed to a root route\'s children to create a route tree, which is then passed to the router.

[](#createroute-options)

## createRoute options 

-   Type: [[RouteOptions]](/router/latest/docs/framework/react/api/router/RouteOptionsType)
-   Required
-   The options that will be used to configure the route instance

[](#createroute-returns)

## createRoute returns 

A new [[Route]](/router/latest/docs/framework/react/api/router/RouteType) instance.

[](#examples)

## Examples 

tsx

![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)

``` 
import  from '@tanstack/react-router'
import  from './__root'

const Route = createRoute(,
  component: IndexComponent,
})

function IndexComponent() </div>
}
```

``` 
import  from '@tanstack/react-router'
import  from './__root'

const Route = createRoute(,
  component: IndexComponent,
})

function IndexComponent() </div>
}
```

</div>
